{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"21f4ece0-ebca-4f75-a7e7-ab72385f7b42","content":"You already have the HotReload extension referenced. To use it, run your tests with `dotnet test` and the `--hotreload` flag:\n\n```\ndotnet test --hotreload\n```\n\nThis starts a **watch-style session** — tests run, then the process stays alive waiting for file changes. When you save a fix to `EmailValidatorTests.cs` (or the code under test), it hot-reloads and **re-runs the tests automatically** without a full rebuild.\n\n**Tips:**\n- Use `--filter` to focus on specific failing tests, e.g.:\n  ```\n  dotnet test --hotreload --filter \"MethodName=YourFailingTest\"\n  ```\n- Press `Ctrl+C` to exit the session.\n\nWant me to start the hot-reload session for you, or help fix the failing tests directly?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"d8f6dabe-dfed-4233-ad21-6f68c7986b41","outputTokens":199},"id":"024eea6f-dc08-454a-835d-5cf8793ad94e","timestamp":"2026-04-07T14:20:51.024Z","parentId":"e46447a3-ef2d-47cc-b9a8-3657d8cd96e7"}
